The paper discusses a model for representing and inferring causal relationships in relational data, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the learning of this model from data, which falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB) and computational complexity (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the implications of the lifted representation on reasoning, which could fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
